The paper deals with the design of communication systems, specifically multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, with limited feedback. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of feedback channels, which is related to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). The use of codebooks and Grassmann packings suggests a connection to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses simulation studies, which could be related to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
